\subsection{Differentiable CVaR via the Dual Representation}\label{ssec:diffcvar}
Let \(C\colon \mathbb{R}^d \to \mathbb{R}\) be a differentiable cost. The CVaR at confidence level \(\beta \in (0,1)\) admits the dual form:
\begin{equation}\label{eq:cvar_dual}
\mathrm{CVaR}_\beta[C] = \max_{\eta\in\mathbb{R}} \left\{\eta - \frac{1}{\beta}
\mathbb{E}\!\left[\max\!\big(C(\boldsymbol{\theta},\mathbf{a})-\eta,0\big)\right]\right\},
\end{equation}
where we approximate the hinge with a linear penalty to ensure the gradient is constant regardless of the cost value.
